        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Additional NTA Species with Fe³⁺\n\nNTA can also form a 1:2 complex (ML₂) with Fe³⁺, with log β₂ values around 24.3 at I = 0.1 M — comparable in magnitude to the 1:1 EDTA complex, but requiring two NTA ligands.\n\n| Beta Definition | Equilibrium | log K (25 °C, I = 0.1 M) |\n|-----------------|-------------|--------------------------|\n| β₂: [ML₂]/[M][L]² | M + 2L ⇌ ML₂ | 24.3 |\n| [MHL]/[ML][H] | ML + H ⇌ MHL | 1.3 |",
