      {
        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "### Chemical Insight\n\nThe ~10 log-unit advantage of EDTA over NTA is a textbook illustration of the **chelate effect** and **denticity**. EDTA wraps around Fe³⁺ with six donor atoms (2 N + 4 carboxylate O), fully satisfying the metal's octahedral coordination sphere in a single ligand. NTA, with only four donor atoms (1 N + 3 carboxylate O), leaves coordination sites available — hence the tendency to form ML₂ species. In practical applications such as water treatment and soil remediation, EDTA's dramatically higher affinity for Fe³⁺ makes it the stronger sequestrant, though NTA is sometimes preferred for its greater biodegradability.\n\n*Source: NIST Standard Reference Database 46 (SRD-46)*",
